[DhtmlXQ_comment0]20120315 2010 cnsc Round 9||Wang Ruixiang L Zheng Yihong||Wang Ruixiang is a relative new comer.||This is one of the longest game that I have translated and annotated. ||The game goes back and forth and then back and forth and then back and forth again...whew.||Praise must be given to the two players for playing such an exciting game.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment6]Wang Ruixiang is a relative new comer. GM Zheng Yihong opted to use this opening to prevent playing the more familiar openings that Wang might have studied and had flying daggers prepared.||GM Zheng Yihong chooses to delay the battleground till midgame with this opening.||The Opposite Direction Cannons was once popular in the 1980's but has gradually fallen out of favor.[/DhtmlXQ_comment6]
[DhtmlXQ_comment7]This is one of the ways that red can play.||A more aggressive approach would be to play R2+6 and it would be filled with fireworks.[/DhtmlXQ_comment7]
