[DhtmlXQ_comment15]And if black accepts the the offer, red would have  increased his lead and have a one move advantage.[/DhtmlXQ_comment15]
[DhtmlXQ_comment19]Although it seems that black can be satisfied with this outcome, red's R8+6 is very aggressive. Wang does not care about black playing R4=7 and shows his determination with this move. ||E3+1 would be the move to make if red opted for a more stable formation.[/DhtmlXQ_comment19]
[DhtmlXQ_comment20]Post-game commentary suggested that this was not very ideal.||When playing the ODC, you tell your opponent that you are going to fight tooth for tooth. By playing C5-1 just does not seem to conform to the spirit of the ODC. (post game commentary by Master Huang Hailin and GM Zhao Xinxin, not me...LOL). The commentary went on to state that whichever side is not brave or fearless enough would suffer losses...[/DhtmlXQ_comment20]
